                    h3 Collecting general information
                    p
                        | When you access this website, general information is automatically tracked.
                        br
                        | For technical reasons, when accessing this website your internet browser automatically transmits data to the web server. Each record
                        | consists of the date and time of access, the URL of the referring web site, the file retrieved, the amount of data sent, the browser
                        | type and version, the operating system and the user's IP address. An allocation of this data to a specific person is not possible.
                        | The stored data will only be evaluated internally and exclusively for statistical purposes.
                    p
                        | GitHub transmits the following data to BTC AG:
                    ul
                        li
                            | Number of visitors to the&nbsp;
                            a(href='https://btc-ag.github.io/') btc-ag.github.io
                            |  website and its child pages
                        li Referrer of the visit
                        li Date and time of the visit
                        li
                            | Visited pages within our website&nbsp;
                            a(href='https://btc-ag.github.io/') btc-ag.github.io
                    p
                        | The following data are additionally collected by GitHub:
                    ul
                        li IP address of the visitor
                        li Technical information, such as operating system and browser of visitors
                        li Language of the browser
                        li Further visited pages within the GitHub offer
                    p
                        | These data are not provided to us. They are collected and used exclusively by GitHub. You can read more about this in the&nbsp;
                        a(href='https://help.github.com/articles/github-privacy-statement/') GitHub Privacy Policy
                        | .
                    p
                        | To protect the security of your data during transmission, GitHub uses state-of-the-art encryption techniques (such as SSL) over HTTPS.
                    h3 Cookies
                    p
                        | Like many other websites, GitHub also uses so-called "cookies" to collect, as noted before, technical information. Cookies are small
                        | text files that are transferred from a website server to your hard drive. Because of this GitHub automatically receives certain data
                        | e.g. IP address, browser, operating system from your computer and your connection to the internet.
                    p
                        | Cookies cannot be used to launch programs or to transfer viruses to a computer.
                    p
                        | The data we collect will not be passed on to third parties.
                    p
                        | Certainly, you can also use our website without cookies. Internet browsers are regularly set to accept cookies. You can deactivate
                        | the use of cookies at any time via the settings of your browser. Please use the help features of your internet browser to find out
                        | how to change these settings. Please note that some features of our website may not work if you have disabled the use of cookies.
                    h3 GitHub login and GitHub registration
                    p
                        | The information you provide, while signing in or registering for a GitHUB-Account, will be used for the purposes specified by GitHub.
                    p
                        | These can be read explicitly in the&nbsp;
                        a(href='https://help.github.com/articles/github-privacy-statement/') GitHub Data Protection Regulation
                        | .
                    h3 Contacting BTC AG
                    p 
                        | If you contact us by e-mail or contact form or register for an event, the information you provide will be stored for the purpose
                        | of processing the request and for possible follow-up questions.
                    p
                        | The data will be processed for the purpose of processing and responding to your request. Data deletion depends on your request. 
                    p
                        | Data processing is carried out in accordance with Art. 6 para. 1 lit. a,b GDPR.
                    h3 Google Analytics
                    p
                        | This website uses Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google Inc. (Google Inc., 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy, Mountain View, CA 94043-1351, USA). Google Analytics uses so-called "cookies",
                        | text files that are stored on your computer to permit an analysis of your use of the website. Usually, the information generated by the cookie
                        | about your use of this website is transmitted to a server of Google in the US and is stored there. On behalf of GitHub, Google will use this
                        | information to evaluate your use of the website, to compile reports on website activity and to provide other services related to website
                        | activity and internet usage to the website operator. The IP address provided by your browser in the context of Google Analytics will not
                        | be merged with other data from Google. You can prevent the storage of cookies by a corresponding setting of your browser software. You can
                        | also prevent the collection and processing of data by Google by downloading the browser AddOn available under the following link:&nbsp;
                        a(href='https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout') https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout
                    p
                        | You can find more information about Google Analytics and Google's privacy policy here:&nbsp;
                        a(href="https://www.google.de/intl/de/policies/privacy/") https://www.google.de/intl/de/policies/privacy/ 
                        | and 
                        a(href="http://www.google.com/analytics/terms/de.html") http://www.google.com/analytics/terms/de.html
                        | .
                    h3 Your rights
                    p
                        | If BTC processes personal data about you, we will provide you on request with information about the categories of data concerned,
                        | the purposes for which the data will be used, any recipients or categories of recipients of the data and the duration of the
                        | planned storage.
                    p
                        | You have the right to request the correction or completion of incorrect or incomplete data.
                    p
                        | If the data processing is based on a consent given by you, you have the right to revoke the consent with effect for the future at any time.
                    p
                        | If data processing is carried out on the basis of a legitimate interest of EWE, you have the right to object to the data processing
                        | for reasons arising from your particular situation (Art. 21 GDPR).
                    p
                        | Under certain circumstances, you have the right to request the deletion of your data. This especially in cases in which the data
                        | is no longer necessary for data processing, you have revoked a given consent or have objected to data processing due to your
                        | particular situation.
                    p
                        | Under certain conditions, you may request the restriction of your personal data if deletion is not possible or the obligation to
                        | delete is in dispute.
                    p
                        | You also have the right to data transferability. This means that we can provide you with your data in a machine-readable format upon request.
                    p
                        | You have the right to contact us directly with regard to a complaint, e.g. the data protection officer of BTC AG. In addition, you can
                        | make an official complaint to the supervisory authority for data protection (Landesbeauftragter für den Datenschutz Niedersachen).
                    h3 Automated individual decision-making (including profiling)
                    p
                        | We do not perform any automated individual decision-making in accordance with article 22 of the GDPR.
                    h3 Security
                    p
                        | BTC uses extensive technical and organisational security measures to protect your personal data managed by us against misuse, accidental
                        | or intentional manipulation or against access by unauthorised persons. Our security procedures are continuously improved in line with
                        | technological developments. 
